The paper proposes algorithms for stochastic optimization and online learning, which are both subfields of machine learning. The use of coordinate descent algorithms suggests that the paper may fall under the optimization category. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions regret performance, which is a common metric in online learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The use of randomized algorithms may also suggest that the paper could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.OC (Optimization and Control). Finally, the mention of convergence rates suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
